    • Constructor Detail

      • Task

        public Task​(java.lang.String taskName,
            TaskTypeEnum type,
            java.time.LocalDate specificTime)
     throws TaskException
        Constructor for Task by passing taskName, type and time. The reason why I customize TaskException is that I don't want Task be created successfully if there's an illegal input. Once the parameters is invalid, I hope this constructor would throw a TaskException to inform above method that there's an error and print out the reason by using Constant.formOutputBySingleString
        Parameters:
        taskName - name of the task
        type - type of the task
        specificTime - time for task stretch information, only valid while type is event/deadline
        Throws:
        TaskException - Once the taskName/time format is invalid, exception would be thrown
